You MAY, for free, today:
  - Read, study, and inspect the AdOff source code.
  - Use AdOff for any purpose, including inside a company / for work
    (internal use is a Permitted Purpose).
  - Modify it and create derivative works.
  - Redistribute it (keeping this license + copyright notices).

You MAY NOT (this is the "Competing Use" restriction):
  - Offer AdOff — or anything with the same/substantially similar
    functionality — as a commercial product or service that competes
    with AdOff. I.e. you cannot resell it, repackage it, or clone it
    as a competing ad blocker product/service.

Automatic open source after 2 years:
  - Each released version of AdOff automatically becomes available under
    the permissive Apache License 2.0 on the SECOND anniversary of its
    release. After that, that version has no Competing-Use restriction.

Scope of this repository:
  - This license covers the inspectable free core: network blocking rules,
    cosmetic filtering, content scripts, background/service worker, UI.
  - The license-validation server and Pro entitlement logic are NOT part
    of this repository and remain proprietary (the real moat).
  - In any conflict, the canonical FSL-1.1-Apache-2.0 terms above govern,
    not this summary.
